===Possessive determiner===
'''their'''

# belonging to them.
:''They will meet tomorrow at their convenience''. 
:''This is probably their cat.'' 
# belonging to someone of unknown gender
:''Everyone must understand their feelings.''

====Usage note====

For centuries, ''their'' has used with a singular antecedent; however, many condemn this usage for its violation of traditional agreement rules. Writers should only use this construction if they are sure it will be viewed as an intentional choice, rather than an error. See [[w:Singular_they|singular they]] for a more in-depth discussion.

